## The Verdict

## **Needs Improvement.**

Your concept is solid. Your design instincts are good. Your plan system is genuinely well-engineered. But the foundation has **5 actively dangerous problems** that would bite you the moment real users show up — and several structural weaknesses that would make adding features increasingly painful.

Here's the honest framing: **you built a working prototype and treated it like a finished product.** The features work, the UI looks professional, the user flows are logical. But the things that separate a prototype from a production SaaS — security, error handling, modularity, scalability — are either missing or half-done.

The good news: none of this requires a rewrite. It's roughly **3-4 days of focused work** to fix everything that matters.

